    "plan_content": "Here is the complete implementation plan for adding `CosineAnnealingScheduler` to the diffusers library.\n\n---\n\n## Plan Summary\n\n### What it does\nA new DDPM-style scheduler where betas follow **cosine annealing**: `β_t = β_min + 0.5·(β_max−β_min)·(1+cos(π·t/T))`. Betas decrease from `beta_end` at t=0 down to `beta_start` at t=T-1. All denoising math is identical to DDPM — only the beta precomputation is novel.\n\n### 5 files to change\n\n| Action | File |\n|--------|------|\n| **Create** | `src/diffusers/schedulers/scheduling_cosine_annealing.py` |\n| **Modify** | `src/diffusers/schedulers/__init__.py` — 2 alphabetical insertions (between `CMStochasticIterativeScheduler` and `DDIMScheduler`) |\n| **Modify** | `src/diffusers/__init__.py` — 2 alphabetical insertions (after `CogVideoXDPMScheduler`) |\n| **Regenerate** | `src/diffusers/utils/dummy_pt_objects.py` — run `python utils/check_dummies.py --fix_and_overwrite` (auto-generated, never edit by hand) |\n| **Create** | `tests/schedulers/test_scheduler_cosine_annealing.py` |\n\n### Key implementation decisions\n- **Beta computation** uses `float64` intermediate precision to avoid rounding drift: `beta_start + 0.5*(beta_end−beta_start)*(1 + torch.cos(math.pi * t_range / T))`\n- All methods (`step`, `add_noise`, `get_velocity`, `set_timesteps`, etc.) are copied verbatim from `DDPMScheduler`; only the output dataclass name and the `\"learned\"` variance branches differ\n- `_compatibles = []` — not part of the Karras-family interchange system\n- The two `test_full_loop_*` numerical assertions must be filled in by running the scheduler once after implementation (standard practice across all DDPM-family test files)",
